1
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:26,000
Belê temaşevanên hêja, vê hefteyê jî me berê xwe da ye…
 
Yes, dear viewers, this week we have turned our way to...

2
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:29,000
Gundê Edamo!
 
Edamo Village!

3
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:49,000
Vê hefteyê jî me berê xwe da ye gundê Edamo, ev gundê Edamo
jî girêdayî navçeya Raco ye. Em ê bi hev ra derbas bibin em
ê bi hev ra gundê Edamo nas bikin.
 
This week as well, we have turned our way to the village of
Edamo, this village of Edamo is tied to the Raco district.
We will go in together and get to know the village of Edamo
together.

4
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:21,000
Belê temaşevanên hêja, sibete xêr be ji we ra. Me ji we re
got em ê derbasî nav zeviyan bibin, em ê nêzikî silavê ke
bidin. Merheba ji we ra, merheba.
 
Yes, dear viewers, good morning to you. We told you we would
pass through the fields, we will approach and say hello.
Hello to you, hello.

5
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:25,000
Merheba, merheba, ehlen we sehlen. Bi xêr hatin, bi ser
çavan re. We oxir û welet rê.
 
Hello, hello, welcome. Welcome, upon my eyes. You have
brought goodness.

6
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:27,000
Em destpêkê we nas bikin?
 
Can we get to know you first?

7
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:30,000
Mihemedê Bekrî Şêxo da li Edamo.
 
Mihemed Bekri Shexo here in Edamo.

8
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:32,000
Li ser çavan Apê Hecî, quwet be ji we ra.
 
Upon my eyes, Uncle Haji, strength to you.

9
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:34,000
Sax bin, sibeta we xêr û xweş, ev cara yekê me dîtîn, hûn…
 
Be well, good and pleasant morning to you, this is the first
time we've seen each other, you...

10
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:38,000
Me got em derbasî gundê Edamo bibin, em a destpêkê jî em
derbasî cem we bûn, me dît hûn li vir kar dikin li vira…
 
We said let's go to Edamo village, and first of all we came
to you, we saw you working here...

11
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:49,000
Li ser sera û li ser çava û em we spas dikin, û ya ehlen we
sehlen, bi oxir û welet rê. Me we dît, we em ziyaret kirin,
serê me bi we bilind e. Û em pir kêfxweş in.
 
Upon my head and eyes, and we thank you, and welcome, you
have brought goodness. We saw you, you visited us, our heads
are held high because of you. And we are very happy.

12
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:55,000
Em jî kêfxweş dibin. Niha ev der quntar e li vir e ne? Ev
quntara çi ye hûn dibêjinê?
 
We are happy as well. Now this place is a valley here, isn't
it? What valley do you call it?

13
00:01:55,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Quntara Mîstik e. Quntara Mîstik wê ra dibêjin.
 
It is the Mistik Valley. They call it the Mistik Valley.

14
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:05,000
Yanî bi giştî gundê, erdnîgariya gund, emaret dikin?
 
So in general the village, the village's geography, are they
cultivating it?

15
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:07,000
Na ev quntar a bi navê xwe diçe.
 
No, this valley goes by its own name.

16
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:10,000
Na ev deştên li vir dibin çi, navê xwe deşta çi ye?
 
No, these plains here, what is the name of the plain?

17
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:16,000
Deşta Wêranşarê wê ra dibêjin, bes, deşta Wêranşarê û deşta
Edamo yanî.
 
They call it the Wêranşar Plain, well, the Wêranşar Plain
and the Edamo Plain.

18
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:20,000
Yanî bi kîjan alî tê naskirin? Deşta Edamo tê naskirin an ya
Wêranşarê?
 
So by which name is it known? Is it known as the Edamo Plain
or Wêranşar?

19
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:23,000
Bi deşta Edamo jî tê naskirin, bi deşta Wêranşarê jî tê
naskirin.
 
It is known as the Edamo Plain, and it is known as the
Wêranşar Plain as well.

20
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:25,000
Ji kîjan alî, kîjan alî… ev…
 
From which side to which side... this...

21
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:35,000
Toximê me, Qerebaba da hudûdê me qerebaba ye, wê ra dibêjin
Kurta Qereço Elî. Ha ev toximê me ye, û başûr e û…
 
Our border is Qerebaba, our border is Qerebaba, they call it
Kurta Qerecho Eli. This is our border, and the south is...

22
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:36,000
Bakurê me jî?
 
And our north?

23
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:39,000
Bakurê me jî Mele Xelîl e, Meydan Ekbez e…
 
Our north is Mele Xelil, Meydan Ekbez...

24
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:42,000
Na Meydan Ekbez na, nagihîje Meydan Ekbeze deşta me?
 
No, not Meydan Ekbez, our plain doesn't reach Meydan Ekbez?

25
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:49,000
Deşta Sêmal e, wê ra dibêjin, tirbe hene li vir derê,
tirbeya Axmeşo heta hewa hedûdê me û Sêmal e.
 
It's the Sêmal Plain, they call it that, there are tombs
here, the tomb of Axmesho, up to there is our border with
Sêmal.

26
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:50,000
Ji alî da jî gundê Meydan Ekbez e…
 
And on that side is Meydan Ekbez village...

27
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:57,000
Gundê Sêmal, paşê tê Meydan Ekbez erê. Deşta me, yanî deşta
Sêmal, paşê tê Meydan Ekbez.
 
Sêmal village, then comes Meydan Ekbez, yes. Our plain, I
mean Sêmal Plain, then comes Meydan Ekbez.

28
00:02:57,000 --> 00:03:04,000
Belê. Qewet be ji we ra. Niha Apê Mihemed gundiyên we, çi li
vir diçînin? Wek navê zeviyan na, navê erdê na?
 
Yes. Strength to you. Now Uncle Mihemed, what do your
villagers plant here? Like, not the names of the fields or
the land?

29
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:15,000
Welleh em genim diçînin. Em berberûka diçînin. Yanî kaffet
el-enwa zirae tiştê ku hebe giştî dibe.
 
Well, we plant wheat. We plant sunflowers. That is, all
kinds of agriculture, whatever there is, everything grows.

30
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:20,000
Hinik jî ava diçînin, hinek jî bejî diçînin.
 
Some plant irrigated crops, some plant rain-fed.

31
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:38,000
Ekteriya me, selef, êtimadî me li ser ava reş bû, ava reş
dihat. Motora avê me hawî dikişandin û xertûm me dirêj
dikir, em pê zirata xwe av didin. Bes noka elhemdulillah her
cih bîr hene. Kulan e, ekteriya xwe li ser bîra tê şandin
noka ev…
 
Most of us, previously, relied on the black water, the black
water would flow. We would run water motors and stretch out
hoses, we would water our crops with it. But now, thank God,
there are wells everywhere. They are dug, mostly they are
irrigated from the wells now this...

32
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:39,000
Ev derî we kolane?
 
Have you dug here?

33
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:47,000
Deşta me gulo re, vê derê me, deşta me kulo ye ber zeftê ra,
eh em nav erdê xwe da bûye çi da kulo ye.
 
Our plain is all... this area of ours, our plain is fully
dug with wells, uh, in our land whatever there is is a well.

34
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:51,000
Û umur dimeşe alhemdulilah. Û ev ava hîn a tê ji sikra dîn
e?
 
And life goes on, thank God. And does this water still come
from that dam?

35
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:58,000
Na noka ev beed feterat na, dêtê… Her deh pênc roj carê ku
tê, pênc roja berdidin…
 
No, now after periods it doesn't come... Every ten, fifteen
days it comes once, they release it for five days...

36
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:06,000
Teb'en li me ra ber nadin, hema ew ji xwedê re berdidin, em
nizanin me'niya çamqê pê penbe di derî xwe ava didin,
çeltîkê xwe ava didin, em jî li vê derê istîfade dibînin jê.
 
Of course they don't release it for us, they release it for
God's sake, we don't know the reason why they water their
cotton, they water their rice, we also benefit from it here.

37
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:10,000
Zaten ew ji benda avê tê, ji Kilisê, ji wî alî te derbasî
Bakur dibe.
 
It already comes from the dam, from Kilis, from that side it
crosses into the North.

38
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:16,000
Ji islehhiyeyê tê, eh. Paşî tê, noka jî, vê fetreyê jî, qut
kirine.
 
It comes from Islahiye, yes. Then it comes, now also, this
period too, they have cut it off.

39
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:21,000
Beriya vê, ez hatim gundê Sêmal av hebû, bes hirî av tinebû
reş bû.
 
Before this, I came to Sêmal village, there was water, but
before that there was no water, it was black.

40
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:28,000
Temam me got, her dehe pênc roja feterake qut dikin. Qey ew
ji wan e ku pêwîstiya gundiya nebe li ser, mera ber nadin,
me'niya xwe berdidin.
 
Exactly, we said, every ten to fifteen days they cut it off
for a period. It must be that they think the villagers don't
need it, they don't release it for us, they release it for
their own reasons.

41
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Li vê derê tu teleb nekin, se- ber nadin.
 
Here if they don't request it, they don't release it.

42
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:34,000
Bîstaniya me xera bibûna, çi bibûna na xema wa giyan e. Hema
xwe ra berdidin.
 
If our orchards were ruined, whatever happened, they
wouldn't care. They just release it for themselves.

43
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:36,000
Bes nawa qe na xeme ku va bîra kola ne…
 
But now they don't have to worry since these wells are
dug...

44
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:39,000
Lê me bîr kulane em elhemdulilleh em qelê xwe dikin hemû
pêwîstiya gundiyan ra.
 
But we have dug wells, thank God, we manage it for all the
needs of the villagers.

45
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:43,000
Ê Apê Mihemed ev nawa çî û çawa diçînin? Nava kundir in e?
 
So Uncle Mihemed, now what do they plant and how? Now there
are melons?

46
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:54,000
Noka, bidayîya gundê, ê buharê, ê buharê, teb'en ce ye,
genim e, silq in e, nîk in e, li vir û şûnda, berberok jî em
diçînin…
 
Now, at the beginning of the village, in the spring, in the
spring, of course it's barley, it's wheat, it's chard, it's
chickpeas, and after that, we plant sunflowers too...

47
00:04:54,000 --> 00:05:03,000
Axirî biharê, axirî biharê em berberok diçînin, berberok jî
pir in, dibin, ceh û me têne rakirin, ba'dî vê tiştî li me
ra kur şûn da mehwsimê me… tê mehwsimê xerîfî.
 
At the end of spring, at the end of spring we plant
sunflowers, sunflowers are plentiful, they grow, barley and
wheat are harvested, after this thing behind us our
season... comes the autumn season.

48
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:08,000
Xeyar, em ekteriya xwe xeyar diçînin, em kundirî mîst
diçînin, ber ku…
 
Cucumbers, we mostly plant cucumbers, we plant small melons,
because...

49
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:09,000
Di vê demê de?
 
At this time?

50
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:16,000
Di vê demê de teb'en… ev payîzokî ye, noka ev xiyarên ha ev
payîzokî ye. Ev kundirên ha… Em kundirên sehhî, destpêkê
biharê ne…
 
At this time, of course... this is autumnal, now these
cucumbers, this is autumnal. These melons... We have actual
melons, at the beginning of spring...

51
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:22,000
Bes payîz e jî dibin, yanî noka şûnda diçênîn ev jî dibin, û
xeyar dibin, xît e diçînin…
 
But they grow in autumn too, I mean, we plant them now and
they grow too, and cucumbers grow, snake cucumbers are
planted...

52
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:30,000
Nacih e yanî, xêr e. Kurbaya me zîde ye. Noka xêr e deşta me
û deşta me de meydanek be ze, xeyar namîşin.
 
It is successful, I mean, it is a blessing. Our soil is
rich. Now thankfully in our plain and Meydan Ekbez plain,
cucumbers don't fail.

53
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:36,000
Wek vî deştê zexm nîn e yanî, wisa ku wexta ku ew nebe wa
nabe, nexweşî ew…
 
It isn't as strong as this plain, meaning, like when it
doesn't grow, it just doesn't, disease or...

54
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:42,000
Wê da ba, a reş û te wê da her cendire se'der da nakin,
bişînin, xêr e, xerbiyê xwe pir e.
 
Over there, the black water and all, over there with every
type of plant they can't grow it, they send it, thank God,
it gets plenty of western wind.

55
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:46,000
Her wiha deşt a Hemqê deşt a Cûmê… Ji vê ra pir çê nabe
yanî…
 
Also the Hemq Plain, the Jum Plain... It doesn't grow well
here, I mean...

56
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:50,000
Çê nabe, xerbiyê xwe pir e. Hawa jê da mêş û xerbî nabin.
 
It doesn't grow, the western wind is too much. With the air
there, insects and the western wind don't let it.

57
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:52,000
Wek Behra Entakye ji vê re derbas…
 
Like the Sea of Antioch passes through here...

58
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:58,000
Ekîd wa ne ye. Lênê hawa domîş xerbî nabe, di domîş şilbiyê
nabin jê xira dibe.
 
For sure it's like that. But without the western wind,
without moisture it doesn't work, it spoils.

59
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:01,000
Tıştê herî ciwan û baş ku dibe çi ye?
 
What is the most beautiful and best thing that grows?

60
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:08,000
Welehî e qeder bîr me, gû tışt e ba, me berî vê pembû diçan,
pembûyî me ulab derdiket.
 
By God, as much as we remember, whatever it was, we used to
plant cotton before this, our cotton would come out great.

61
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:13,000
Lê erdiyê me kûr in, erdiyê me xedar in, erdiyê me yanî
seyin tace te di de.
 
Because our lands are deep, our lands are strong, our lands
give you yield.

62
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:21,000
Ku seyî zanin yeek gî zebeşî xizmetî bike, em di tucar erdan
re ra dikin. Nokê şûna wê genim min kiriye xiyar.
 
If a person knows how to take care of watermelons properly,
we can do commerce on the lands. Now instead of wheat I've
planted cucumbers.

63
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:24,000
Ev a min bi qesir gênim em ê lê bidin.
 
I will cut this like wheat.

64
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:29,000
De behsa pembû bike, berê Efrînê pir pembû diçan, naha kes
naçîne, pir kêm e…
 
Come on, talk about cotton, Afrin used to plant a lot of
cotton, now no one plants it, it's very rare...

65
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:36,000
E na mehlîce neman der neman, kesî istîlam bike, teslîm
bibin, kesî teslîm kirin, istîlam bihe tenê ye…
 
Eh no, there are no cotton gins left, no places left, no one
to receive it, to deliver it, whoever delivered it, to
receive it is the only thing...

66
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:39,000
Bi dehan cezîre dar e hemî pembû diçandin yanî.
 
With dozens of islands of trees, they used to plant all
cotton, I mean.

67
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:43,000
Hele… Ê xeyo mehlîce divê derê hene, zeyt mektebe di gel de
hene…
 
Yes... Brother, there are cotton gins here, there are olive
oil presses with them...

68
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:44,000
Çima we zeytûn?
 
Why did you [plant] olives?

69
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:50,000
Cema Zeytûn jî pir in e erê, bes ne we me pembû jî diçan, bo
deştan û xerciyê pênc bîrî, pembû jî rind e necahî ye.
 
The olive crowd is also large, yes, but not like we used to
plant cotton too, for the plains and the expense of five
wells, cotton is also good and successful.

70
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:55,000
Bes her kî wa meşa kûne bîna dar bînin, kesek ma teslîm bivê
hîtê na ye pembû.
 
But whoever walks that way and brings trees, there's no one
left to deliver it to, so cotton didn't continue.

71
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:58,000
Naha wa tu behsa xeyare jî. Xeyare jî dibin…
 
Now you're talking about cucumbers too. Cucumbers grow as
well...

72
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:01,000
Na xeyara… Xeyara pirr in necih in ceme.
 
No, cucumbers... Cucumbers are very successful for us.

73
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:06,000
Xeyara licema dibin û deştî me de nebe deştî me de meydanê
dibin feqet la xer.
 
Cucumbers grow with us, and if not in our plain, they grow
in the plain of Meydan [Ekbez], strictly there.

74
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:15,000
Ta bedî te baha ziraate ke te gû çi di çîn in. Me hincîra di
çandin ne na cîha ne. Me hinar ço dın e, nêcî hîne. Deştî ne
dîn tê ki zengîn in.
 
So after you talk about agriculture, you said what do they
plant. We planted figs, they are not successful. We planted
pomegranates, they are not successful. Our plain is a place
that is rich.

75
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:21,000
Zeytûnî ku, ncî hene. Yanê bawan deşt a birro noke. Û na
deşt gî yanî.
 
Olives are successful. Meaning these plains can grow them
now. And not every plain, I mean.

76
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:23,000
Tu deşta wext we çi na hên e.
 
In your plain, when you don't bring anything.

77
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:26,000
Na evan fêqiya, evan darê fêqiya wek sêv…
 
No, these fruits, these fruit trees like apples...

78
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:28,000
Fêqiyê havinê? Şeftelî û ê wisa…
 
Summer fruit? Peaches and things like that...

79
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:29,000
Tu nîn e ha. Tu nîn e.
 
None at all. None.

80
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:30,000
Wisa ne wisa…
 
Like this, not like this...

81
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:36,000
Vê da dîse çend ne, hona çendin yane di çîn me kerd. Yanî
tibe çi di deşt a cim a he be.
 
There, again they plant some, they planted some there, I
mean we did it. I mean whatever there is in the Cume Plain.

82
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:37,000
Yanî natîbiçê li deşta Cûmê hebe.
 
I mean, they don't bring what is in the Cume Plain.

83
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:45,000
Ne tinene, îna nokim ne o tîne, hewna pa te te dar e di
çîne, na xiyar ceme ne mêşîne. Xiyar cema na mêşîne. Hemt e
da deşt qirra wî bi wa gije mene necehin.
 
There aren't any, here I won't say I bring them, they plant
trees there, but cucumbers don't fail here. Cucumbers don't
fail for us. Even the Qereba plain is not successful like
this place.

84
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:48,000
Ezi ji xatirê xwe ji te bixwazim. Quwet be ji we ra.
 
I would like to say goodbye to you. Strength to you.

85
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:50,000
Silavet xweş. Spas ji we re.
 
Nice greetings. Thank you.

86
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:51,000
Xatirê te.
 
Goodbye.

87
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:58,000
Bi selamet. Ehlen û sehlen. Em spas dikin. Oxir û welet.
Saetên we xweş. We em zîyaret kirin. Pir bi kêfxweşî.
 
Go in peace. Welcome. We thank you. You have brought
goodness. Have a good time. You visited us. With great
pleasure.

88
00:07:58,000 --> 00:08:14,000
Em jî spas dikin.
 
We thank you too.

89
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:24,000
Şêniyên gund da barajiyana xwe bi çandiniyê dikin. Ji
xwedîkirina zeviyên zeytûnan, baxçeyên sebzeyan û dexilê.
 
The residents of the village make their living through
agriculture. From tending to olive groves, vegetable
gardens, and grain.

90
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:30,000
Di gel çandiniyê, hîn malbat, sewalên jî xwedî dikin. Û
debara jiyana malbata xwe, jê peyda dikin.
 
Along with agriculture, some families also raise livestock.
And they provide for their family's living from it.

91
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:36,000
Terzîxaneyek bi nav û deng li Efrînê heye, ku baştirîn
xortên gund li vir dixebitin.
 
There is a famous tailoring shop in Afrin, where the best
young men of the village work here.

92
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:56,000
Her wiha hejmarek ji jin û mêran wek karmend di sazî û
desteyên Rêveberiya Xweser da, li Raco û Efrînê dixebitin.
 
Furthermore, a number of men and women work as employees in
the institutions and boards of the Autonomous Administration
in Raco and Afrin.

93
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:06,000
Dayê merheba ji we re.
 
Mother, hello to you.

94
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:07,000
Merheba.
 
Hello.

95
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:08,000
Em destpêkê we nas bikin?
 
Can we get to know you first?

96
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:09,000
Henîfe.
 
Henife.

97
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:10,000
Ser çava.
 
Upon my eyes.

98
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:12,000
Emîne.
 
Emine.

99
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:13,000
Xweşî ser çavê min.
 
Gladly, upon my eyes.

100
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:14,000
Faîze.
 
Faize.

101
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:16,000
Xweşî ser çavê min.
 
Gladly, upon my eyes.

102
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:18,000
Dayê destên we sax bin.
 
Mother, bless your hands.

103
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:19,000
Yê te jî sax bin.
 
Yours too.

104
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:27,000
Va jî tiştekî xwemalî ye, tiştê xwe yi ji we jîna rêt çiya
diya xwa wek ku jê aniye. Ka hinek ji me ra qala wê bike û
çi hazir kirine va?
 
This is also something homemade, your own thing that you
have kept from your mother just as she brought it. So tell
us a bit about it and what have they prepared here?

105
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:34,000
Ha va, torosê me ye, ha va dayîka me ji pişta me hane
kiriye.
 
This, this is our heritage, this our mother kept for us from
behind.

106
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:43,000
Ev a zihnet a da me, ku hane bikin. Me jî kir aqilê xwe û me
kir. Ne?
 
This is a craft that they gave us to do. We also kept it in
mind and we did it. Right?

107
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:58,000
Ha va mehnî nezer e, yak… Û bihundura… Riza lek, ew ta yî
gund, li çi dibin, û em li mal diçînin. Eşt a ha va karê me
ye. Ne?
 
This is to ward off the evil eye, one... And inside... Riza
lek, the threads of the village, what they are used for, and
we weave at home. This is our work. Right?

108
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:00,000
Erê. Ê dayê, bi rastî ev a…
 
Yes. So mother, really this...

109
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:05,000
Me ra di derbasbûna gund da bê, te dîtin her malekê da heye
yan na?
 
Tell us about when you pass through the village, did you see
if it's in every house or not?

110
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:10,000
Lê me ra gund da, yanî tebî tebî di pirran da heye.
 
Well, in our village, naturally, it's in most houses.

111
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:12,000
Yanî paş û pêşiya bûkê jî dişewitînin. Da utîne.
 
They even burn it behind and in front of the bride. Then
they bring it.

112
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:13,000
Ew ji bo çi ye?
 
What is that for?

113
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:16,000
Ev ji bo çav e. Bûk çav nebin.
 
That is for the evil eye, so the bride doesn't catch the
evil eye.

114
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:20,000
Na, dema derê bûkê anîna?
 
No, when they bring the bride to the door?

115
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:22,000
Wextî li dîdanê anîna.
 
Yes, when they show her, and then bring her.

116
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:24,000
Berê lê naha?
 
In the past or now?

117
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:25,000
Berê jî û noka jî.
 
In the past, and also now.

118
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:28,000
Dema berê bûk li hespê da dikirin û dadanîn...
 
In the past, when they would put the bride on a horse and
bring her...

119
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:30,000
Dîsa wisa dikirin. Wextî dadanîn hundirî,
 
They did the same. When they would bring her inside,

120
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:32,000
dîsa di pêşîyê de dişewitandin.
 
again they would burn it in front of her.

121
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:34,000
Me'neya wê çav e.
 
Its meaning is the evil eye.

122
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:35,000
Na. Ev e?
 
No. What is this?

123
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:38,000
Ev e, zenaeta dêka min e.
 
This is, you know, my mother's craft.

124
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:41,000
Û li mala xwe hane dikirin û bi hundirê xwe ve xistin.
 
And for us... they put it inside the door.

125
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:44,000
Ê ji bo nezerê hûn çi çêdikin? Başqeyî wê tiştekî din jî
heye?
 
And for the evil eye, what do you make? Is there anything
else besides this?

126
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:46,000
Na. Na.
 
No. No.

127
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:49,000
Silav, em vî darikî çawa çêdikin?
 
Greetings, how do we make this stick?

128
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:52,000
Paşê em vê û vê ve çêdikin, ewê gindor...
 
Later we make it with this and this, the round one...

129
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:54,000
Vê, vê û vê.
 
This, this and this.

130
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:57,000
Paşê em benikê tê ra dikin.
 
Then we put the string through it.

131
00:10:57,000 --> 00:11:00,000
Û ez paşê jê ra vedixim. Vê benîkê jî çêdikin...
 
And later I set it up. They also make this string...

132
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:02,000
Ez tê da vedixim.
 
I put it through it.

133
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:03,000
Û ev dar derdixin.
 
And they take this stick out.

134
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:06,000
Di her hundirê gund da heye?
 
Is it in every house in the village?

135
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:10,000
Malan da heye. Di pirran da heye, di hinek da nîne. Gundiya
da nîne.
 
It is in the houses. Most have it, some don't. In the
villages, it's not.

136
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:13,000
Bes mala gundê we da di hemûyan da, di gundiyan da hebû?
 
But in the houses of your village, did everyone in the
village have it?

137
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:15,000
Welleh ez nizanim, ev demên berê bûn.
 
By God, I don't know, these were the old times.

138
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:19,000
Yanî ez zanim noka li mala me da heye, lê li malên din da
tune.
 
I mean, I know we have it in our house now, but in other
houses there isn't.

139
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:21,000
Ne. Bes ev rind e, ji bo çi te çêdikir?
 
No. But this is nice, why did you make it?

140
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:23,000
Ev e... ev rinde.
 
This is, this is nice.

141
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:25,000
Ev tiştek e wek... Navê wê çi ye?
 
This is something like... What is its name?

142
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:26,000
Na...
 
No...

143
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:29,000
Tu karî di rojekê da çêkî, qedî?
 
Can you finish making it in one day?

144
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:30,000
Na le...
 
No...

145
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:31,000
Di saetekê qedî?
 
Does it finish in an hour?

146
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:33,000
Du saet, sê saet meriv dida ser dadiqediya.
 
A person works on it for two, three hours to finish.

147
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:36,000
Dayîka te tiştek ji te ra çêdikir?
 
Did your mother make some for you?

148
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:37,000
Lê.
 
Yes.

149
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:40,000
Dayîka min ji min ra çêdikir, em piçek jê hîn bûn.
 
My mother used to make it for me, we learned a little from
her.

150
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:41,000
Te ji keça xwe ra jî hîn kir?
 
Did you teach it to your daughter too?

151
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:44,000
Welle keça min nizane. Keçeke min bi tenê heye, ew jî
nizane.
 
By God, my daughter doesn't know. I only have one daughter,
and she doesn't know either.

152
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:46,000
Min hîn nekir.
 
I didn't teach her.

153
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:51,000
Tiştek dayîka te çi bîra te bûye? Yanî dema dayîka te tiştek
bi kar dianî û çêdikir, ew bîra te bûye?
 
What do you remember from your mother? I mean, when your
mother used to use and make something, do you remember that?

154
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:53,000
Tiştek bîra min nebûye.
 
I don't remember anything.

155
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:54,000
Hûn hemû tiştan çêdikin?
 
Do you make all the things?

156
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:55,000
Lê lê.
 
Yes, yes.

157
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:58,000
Em vî cilî çêdikin. Em vê benê çêdikin.
 
We make this rug now. We make this yarn now.

158
00:11:58,000 --> 00:12:00,000
Yanî gelê, pênc şeş mînak şol çêdikim.
 
I mean, you used to do about five types of work.

159
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:03,000
Ez dixwazim bipirsim,
 
You, you... I want to ask,

160
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:05,000
Dayîka te ji ben hez dikir?
 
Did your mother also prepare the string?

161
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:07,000
Ka ji min ra hinek behsa ben bikî.
 
Can you tell me a little bit about the string?

162
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:11,000
Behsa ben, em diheriyan dirêstin.
 
About the string, we used to spin it.

163
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:13,000
Em diçûn dar ji bo wê dikirin.
 
We went to fetch wood for it.

164
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:14,000
Hûn li kuderê bo wê dar dikirin?
 
Where did you fetch wood for it?

165
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:20,000
Li çiyayê gundê me da. Wekî Raco, wekî Efrînê, di çiyayê wan
de heyebû.
 
In the mountains of our village. Like Raco, like Afrin, they
were in the mountains there.

166
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:21,000
Dê û bavê me bo me çêdikirin.
 
Our parents used to make it for us.

167
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:25,000
Me'neya wê, da bibe hîmê mala mîrê xwe. Aslê xwe neherime.
 
Its meaning is that it becomes the foundation of her
husband's house. So she doesn't ruin her roots.

168
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:26,000
Ê, ev benê we bi xwe çêkiriye?
 
And, did you make this string yourselves?

169
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:32,000
Me bi xwe çêkiriye. Me zanîbû em, yanî wextê em derdiketin,
ji me ra heft korik bi ben dikirin.
 
We made it ourselves. Yes, we knew it, I mean when we were
leaving, they made seven loops with string for us.

170
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:36,000
Ji bo me'neya wê hûn jî bigihêjin heftan, ev her tim divê ha
çêbibe.
 
Because its meaning is that you also reach seven, this will
always be like this.

171
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:37,000
Ji bo çi ye divê ha çêbibe?
 
Why should it be like this?

172
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:39,000
Ew me'neye, ta pêşê da.
 
This means, they gave a thread first.

173
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:41,000
Pê nafê, te mehkem dibe.
 
With the navel, you become strong.

174
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:42,000
Li xwe neherime.
 
So she doesn't get ruined.

175
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:44,000
Yanî, divê ew wisa çêbikin?
 
You mean, they must make it like that?

176
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:46,000
hawa na, dema tu kal dikin,
 
Like no, when they get old,

177
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:48,000
bi dasiyan çêdikin,
 
they make it with a sickle,

178
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:50,000
û tevlî hev dikin, dikin ben.
 
and they mix it together, they make string.

179
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:52,000
Me'neya wê tu hişk debî.
 
Its meaning is that you should be strong.

180
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:56,000
Me'neya wê we nabe.
 
Its meaning is it won't be like that.

181
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:59,000
Ê, ev yanî, taybet ji bo çi çêdikirin vî benî?
 
And, this I mean, what did they especially make this string
for?

182
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:04,000
Ji bo pêçan. Cîhizê gundê da, mala piştî gundê, pê mala xwe
bar kirin.
 
For swaddling. The dowry in the village, the house behind
the village, they loaded their house with it.

183
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:09,000
Berê bavê wan, bavê wî bar dikirin. Bûk dihat û cîhiz. Bûk û
zava tenê bûn.
 
In the past, their father, his father would load it. The
bride came with the dowry. There was only the bride and the
groom.

184
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:13,000
Pê cîhizê gundê da, tiştên gundê pê diştandin.
 
With the dowry in the village, they tied the village things
with it.

185
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:17,000
Yanî dema dêyek çêdikir, ji keça xwe ra çêdikir.
 
I mean when a mother made it, she made it for her daughter.

186
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:20,000
Erê, ji keça xwe ra çêdikir. Wextê keça xwe derxist didayê.
 
Yes, she made it for her daughter. When her daughter was
leaving, she gave it to her.

187
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:23,000
Me'neya çûyîna mala xwe. Me'neya wê...
 
The meaning of going to her house. Its meaning...

188
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:25,000
Ber bi çava mala xwe ne dida?
 
Why didn't she give it to her house?

189
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:27,000
Ev bi qîzê xwe da derbas bû.
 
This was passed to her daughter.

190
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:28,000
Pê rekoyê jî.
 
With the swaddle too.

191
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:30,000
Tev rûbên gundê da derxistin. Paşê nedan.
 
With all the village clothes, they took it out. Then they
didn't give it back.

192
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:32,000
Gundiya ewa dikirin, yanî malbata kê kur dibe, gundiya
radikirin?
 
The villagers used to do that, I mean, the family of whoever
had a son, the villagers would take it?

193
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:35,000
Kê kur dikir, lê kî bi kok be wê radikir. Lê rana dikir...
 
Whoever had a boy, but whoever was strong would pick her up.
But if they didn't...

194
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:40,000
Dirakir. Zanî saxiye. Guh nedan. Zanî nexweşiya wê bûkê...
 
They would pick her up. They knew she was healthy. They
ignored it. They knew the illness of that bride...

195
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:41,000
Ê wisa, wisa dibû.
 
And so, it was like that.

196
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:44,000
Hawa jî hebû. Tecrûbeya gundê pêk dihat...
 
There was that too. A village experience was happening...

197
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:45,000
Tecrûbeyeke zehf dirêj çêkir.
 
She had a very long experience.

198
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:46,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

199
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:49,000
Kûrî berê biquwet rabûn. Pê tiştên xwa diştandin.
 
The boys in the past grew up strong. They used to tie their
things with it.

200
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:53,000
Pê mislê yek pê radibû, yek pişkek di navê da...
 
Like for example one would get up with it, one would put a
piece in the middle...

201
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:57,000
Wekî tiştê berê, mirov xurt nebûn.
 
Like the things in the past, people were not strong.

202
00:13:57,000 --> 00:14:00,000
Pê diştandin, dianîn malê.
 
They tied it with it, brought it home.

203
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:05,000
Li malê biniştana, radikirina, gerek ku bî e di şandina...
 
At home if they sat down, if they picked it up, if they had
to they would send it...

204
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:09,000
Ê tune. Cîranan dihatin daxwaz meselen, didanê.
 
And if they didn't have it. Neighbors would come and ask for
it for example, they gave it.

205
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:10,000
Hawa jî çêdibû.
 
It happened like that too.

206
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:18,000
Em nizanim ev dem maye, ne me yek kiriye. Tiştkî rastin, gî
çêdikin, cî bi we dikin.
 
I don't know if this time has remained, we haven't done it.
True things, they make all, they do things with it.

207
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:20,000
Yanî ji bo hîmê karê çi di malê da heye pê dikirin?
 
I mean, did they do it with it for the foundation of
whatever work is in the house?

208
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:24,000
Teqicikên jinan hildigirtin, berê diçûn şalakan.
 
They picked up women's spindles, they used to go to
swaddling.

209
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:26,000
Şalekan ji wî benî.
 
Swaddling with that string.

210
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:27,000
Belê. Şalakan.
 
Yes. Swaddling.

211
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:30,000
Erê. Pê jinan dikirin. Tiştina navda.
 
Yes. The women did it with it. Things inside.

212
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:32,000
Pê me'nî korê xwe vebikin.
 
With the meaning to open their loops.

213
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:34,000
Pê xurî xweş tişt dikin.
 
They do nice things with wool.

214
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:36,000
Li xwe neherimin.
 
So they don't get ruined.

215
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:37,000
Ya wisa jî.
 
It's like that too.

216
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:40,000
Xwestiya bi wan nedada, em dizanin lê dayika te tiştên ha ra
çêkiriye?
 
The suitor didn't give to them, we know but did your mother
make these things for you?

217
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:41,000
Na.
 
No.

218
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:42,000
Lê?
 
No?

219
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:46,000
Dibên, yanî xêra dêka te, xesûya te, vî benî te re çêkir?
 
They say, I mean the goodness of your mother, your mother-
in-law, did she make this string for you?

220
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:48,000
Yanî me ewe xwe nîne, bas çe...
 
I mean we don't have it ourselves, but what...

221
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:50,000
Şûrek li me da dixistin.
 
They struck us with a sword.

222
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:52,000
Yanî her malekê gerek benekî wisa hebe?
 
I mean, does every house need to have such a string?

223
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:57,000
Erê, her malekê gerek benekî wê hebe. Xêra te qîzê xwe da,
gerek korikî xwe girtibe.
 
Yes, every house needs to have its own string. For the
goodness of your daughter, she must have held her loop.

224
00:14:57,000 --> 00:15:01,000
Ger tu nizanîbî ew çi ye, dê bêjin dêka te ji min re ev banê
te re çêkiriye.
 
If you don't know what it is, they will say your mother made
this string for you.

225
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:06,000
Xêra te... Qîz kê ban dasti dayîkê da, bal mirov kor e.
 
Your goodness... The girl who tied the mother's string, is
blind among people.

226
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:11,000
Bi keça me re jî mezin e. Gundekî xirîb e.
 
She is also big with our daughter. It's a foreign village.

227
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:15,000
Ka mera carek bi dayê ji bo... Dayê merhaba, çawa yî? Te
carê de.
 
Come tell us once about the mother... Hello mother, how are
you?

228
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:17,000
Ehlan we sehlan. Çawa yî?
 
Welcome. How are you?

229
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:18,000
Tu karî hinek tiştên me re, ser karî xwe, deng kî?
 
Can you talk to us a bit about your work?

230
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:21,000
Ez vê tenşîyê darêsim. Benan çêdikim.
 
I am spinning this thread. Making strings.

231
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:22,000
Kurkên me hevin...
 
We have jackets...

232
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:26,000
Ev ci, bi dayîkê xwe fêr bû? Dayîkê te jî pêş de te te
çêdikir.
 
Who learned this from their mother? Your mother also made it
for you before.

233
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:29,000
Pênîr çêdikim. Şîr genim dikim. Dimeyînim.
 
I make cheese. I make milk and wheat. I ferment it.

234
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:32,000
Qîza te re jî ben ha di dayê?
 
Did you give such a string to your daughter too?

235
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:33,000
Min tev dabin e.. Tev dayê.
 
I gave it to all. I gave it.

236
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:34,000
Têşen şitê.
 
You wash it.

237
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:38,000
Ben, daran. Ew mezin min elman... Banaan wekî wan.
 
Strings, woods. That big one... Strings like them.

238
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:43,000
Wa te çil, cila çêdikir derî da? Cila li hemî gundiya berî
dayîkê beri hamî cila çêdikir, qê jî çêdikir?
 
Did you make clothes outside? Did you make clothes for all
the villagers before, did she make all the clothes?

239
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:45,000
Çêdikirin ok jî. Çênekirin.
 
They made that too. They didn't make it.

240
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:48,000
Çêdikirin cil û cubik ji çêdikir.
 
They made clothes and coats too.

241
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:50,000
Hav. Kerem bike.
 
This. Here you go.

242
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:52,000
Espasi xwe re. Saeta te xweş.
 
Thank you. Bless your time.

243
00:15:52,000 --> 00:16:12,000
Sata te xweş be. Xweda ji te razî be.
 
Bless your time. May God be pleased with you.

244
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:54,000
Gundê Adama, girêdayî navçeya Raco ya Kantona Efrînê ye.
 
The village of Adama is connected to the Raco district of
the Afrin Canton.

245
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:56,000
21 kîlometreyan li bakurê navçeya Raco,
 
21 kilometers north of the Raco district,

246
00:16:56,000 --> 00:17:00,000
50 kîlometreyan li bakurê bajarê Efrînê dikeve.
 
it is located 50 kilometers north of the city of Afrin.

247
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:04,000
Herwiha sê kîlometreyan nêzî sînorê Bakurê Kurdistanê ye.
 
Also, it is three kilometers close to the border of Northern
Kurdistan.

248
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:09,000
Navê gund ji navê kesê yekemîn ku di gund de niştecih bûye,
hatiye.
 
The name of the village comes from the name of the first
person who settled in the village.

249
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:13,000
Tê gotin ku, di berê de, du bera bi navê Edem û Cela hebûn.
 
It is said that, in the past, there were two brothers named
Edem and Cela.

250
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:15,000
Cela gundê Cela ava kir,
 
Cela built the village of Cela,

251
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:17,000
û herwiha Edem jî li vir niştecih bû,
 
and Edem also settled here,

252
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:20,000
û navê gund bo Adema ma.
 
and the name of the village remained as Adama.

253
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:24,000
Gundê Adema berê li deşta Wêranşarê bû,
 
The village of Adama used to be in the plain of Wêranşar,

254
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:26,000
lê piştre xelkê gund li çiya niştecih bûn.
 
but later the village's people settled in the mountains.

255
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:29,000
Hejmara xaniyên gund 110 xanî ne.
 
The number of houses in the village is 110.

256
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:33,000
Û hejmara niştecihan nêzî hezar û sed kes in.
 
And the number of inhabitants is close to one thousand one
hundred people.

257
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:36,000
Pirtirê xelkê gund ji eşîra Celaliyan e.
 
Most of the people in the village are from the Celali tribe.

258
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:56,000
Hêjayî bîrxistinê ye ku gundekî din bi heman navî heye, li
ser xetê ye, ango li Bakurê Kurdistanê li hember hev in.
 
It is worth mentioning that there is another village with
the same name, it is on the border, meaning in Northern
Kurdistan they are opposite each other.

259
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:10,000
Merheba Birê Rêdwan.
 
Hello Mr. Rêdwan.

260
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:16,000
Merheba. Ehlen we sehlen ji bo hatina we ya li qenala Ronahî
ra û bi taybet bernameya Xelat ra.
 
Hello. Welcome for your coming to the Ronahi channel and
especially the Xelat program.

261
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:20,000
Ku hatine, ser serê me, li ser çavên me li gundê Adama.
 
That you have come, upon our heads, upon our eyes in the
village of Adama.

262
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:22,000
Gelek spas ji we re, mala we ava be.
 
Thank you very much, may your house prosper.

263
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:26,000
Em destpêkê dikarin bibêjin ku gundê Adama ji kuderê hatiye?
 
Can we say from the beginning where the village of Adama
came from?

264
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:33,000
Yanî, eşîrek e, yan jî malbatek e, yan kesên ji hev cûda ne?
Û navê gund ji ku hatiye?
 
I mean, is it a tribe, or a family, or people different from
each other? And where did the name of the village come from?

265
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:37,000
Navê gundê me ji koka me hatiye.
 
The name of our village comes from our root.

266
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:41,000
Adema û Cela.
 
Adema and Cela.

267
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:45,000
Belê, em dema derbasî gundê Cela bûn, bi rastî ew behsa we
dikirin, gotin pismamên me ne.
 
Yes, when we passed into the village of Cela, truly they
talked about you, they said they are our cousins.

268
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:47,000
Cela pismamên me ne.
 
Cela are our cousins.

269
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:50,000
Berê li vê derê, em rûniştibûn.
 
In the past, we had settled in this place.

270
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:53,000
Di navbera Cela û di navbera Adema de pirsek hatibû vekirin.
 
Between Cela and Adema a problem had opened up.

271
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:55,000
Û em jî li vir man.
 
And we stayed here.

272
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:58,000
Behsa goristanê kirin, ko turbeyên we hene, li vir jî hene?
 
They talked about the graveyard, that you have tombs, are
there some here too?

273
00:18:58,000 --> 00:19:00,000
Turbeyên me hene, li pêşiya Cela hene.
 
We have tombs, there are some in front of Cela.

274
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:03,000
Û li pêşiya Xelîlalka jî hene.
 
And there are some in front of Xelilalka too.

275
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:06,000
Ê berê gundê we li ku derê bû? Berê kî ku hûn derbasî vî
cihî bibin.
 
And where was your village in the past? Before you crossed
into this place.

276
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:10,000
Gundê me di wê deştê de bû, wê deşta li hember.
 
Our village was in that plain, that plain opposite.

277
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:14,000
Yanî li wî sînorî, yanî berê wexta sînor tune bû,
 
I mean at that border, I mean in the past when there was no
border,

278
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:16,000
gundê me di wê deştê de bû.
 
our village was in that plain.

279
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:21,000
Em li wê derê bûn. Paşê, perçeyek li me çûye Bakurê
Kurdistanê.
 
We were there. Then, a part of us went to Northern
Kurdistan.

280
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:22,000
Ew jî Adema ye.
 
That is also Adema.

281
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:25,000
Û em perçek jî hatine vî alî.
 
And a part of us came to this side.

282
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:27,000
Nêzîkî sînorê kîjan deran e, yanî?
 
Near the border of which places, I mean?

283
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:30,000
Nêzîkî Xosê ye.
 
Near Xose.

284
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:32,000
Çend kîlometreyan nêzîk e, yan dûr e?
 
How many kilometers is it near, or far?

285
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:36,000
Nêzîk e, şazdeh kîlometre teqriben li hemberî me ye.
 
It is near, approximately sixteen kilometers opposite us.

286
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:39,000
Û meyrika me ye, em jî meyrika wan e.
 
And they are our lineage, we are also their lineage.

287
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:46,000
Berê sînor ku li ser çênebû, te sînor vî derê bi carekê tune
bû.
 
In the past when the border wasn't made, there was no border
here at all.

288
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:49,000
Piştî ku sînor çêbû, ev gundê we hat derbaskirin ji aliyê vî
da?
 
After the border was made, this village of yours was crossed
from this side?

289
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:51,000
Piştî sînor, gundê me derbasî vî alî bû.
 
After the border, our village crossed to this side.

290
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:54,000
Wan li wê derê, em jî bi wê derê bi rûniştin.
 
They over there, and we settled over there.

291
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:57,000
Naha ev cihê gundê we, ev ji serê çiya ye ka çi ye?
 
Now this place of your village, is it on top of a mountain
or what?

292
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:59,000
Ev çiya ye bi navê Çiyayê Kevirê...
 
This is a mountain by the name of Mount Kevir...

293
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:00,000
Çi navê wê?
 
What is its name?

294
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:02,000
Gundê we çi... navê wî çiye?
 
Your village... what is its name?

295
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:04,000
Navê wî Çelîşîn... Geleqa.
 
Its name is Çelîşîn... Geleqa.

296
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:09,000
Û ev gundê me li ser sê geliyan çêbûye. Geliyê Çîlo...
 
And this village of ours is built on three valleys. The
valley of Çîlo...

297
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:15,000
...geliyê Banê, û geliyê Silo.
 
...the valley of Banê, and the valley of Silo.

298
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:18,000
Ey gundê we nêzî sînor e jixwe?
 
And your village is close to the border, right?

299
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:22,000
Deştê we jî piraniya wê li aliyê sînor ketiye ne wisa?
 
Most of your plains have fallen on the side of the border,
hasn't it?

300
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:30,000
Gundê me niha sê kîlometre ji sînor ve dûr e. Û wek sê sed
hektar erdê me li aliyê sînor e, û xeta mayîna ye.
 
Our village is now three kilometers away from the border.
And about three hundred hectares of our land is on the side
of the border, and it is a minefield.

301
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:31,000
Ew bi dest kî de ne?
 
In whose hands are they?

302
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:35,000
Ew bi dest tirkan de ye. Yanî aliyê Bakur de ye.
 
It is in the hands of the Turks. I mean, it is on the side
of the North.

303
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:41,000
Ew jî meyre me ne, naha ka hêli dîtin dîtin hinek jî di bin
bumbeyan de maye.
 
Those are also our lands, some of them are now clearly seen
to be left under bombs.

304
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:44,000
Yanî erdê we bi dest miletê we de ne. Dîsa qismek jê di bin
bumbeyan de maye ne wisa?
 
So your land is in the hands of your people. Still, a part
of it is left under bombs, right?

305
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:50,000
Hinek bi dest meyre me de ye... ê... wek 150 hektor jî di
bin bumbeyan de maye.
 
Some of it is in our hands... uh... about 150 hectares is
left under bombs.

306
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:51,000
Yanî hudûd e.
 
I mean, it is the border.

307
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:53,000
Yanî sînor ev e di nav erdê we de ye.
 
So this is the border right in the middle of your land.

308
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:55,000
Sînor... erê ev e bi ser erdê me de ye.
 
The border... yes, this is it over our land.

309
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:57,000
Berê sînor nedihat xuyakirin.
 
Before, the border couldn't be seen.

310
00:20:57,000 --> 00:21:00,000
Û niha, ev gundê we... Gundê Ademo...
 
And now, this village of yours... The village of Ademo...

311
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:02,000
Çend xanî tê de hene?
 
How many houses are in it?

312
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:06,000
Gundê Ademo, naha wek... 110 xanî ne.
 
The village of Ademo, right now is about... 110 houses.

313
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:09,000
Malbat çend tê de ne? Naha bi giştî malbat in?
 
How many families are in it? Are they mostly family?

314
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:18,000
Niha bi giştî tê de bi xwerê bibêjin silav. Em 6 malbat
asasiyê vî gundî ne. Lê dû re malbat hatine.
 
Now generally, first say greetings to yourselves. 6 of our
families are the foundation of this village. But later,
other families came.

315
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:21,000
Naha teqrîben em 10 malbat in.
 
Right now we are approximately 10 families.

316
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:24,000
Û em gişt xizm û birayên hev in.
 
And we are all relatives and brothers of each other.

317
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:30,000
Û ez dikarim wan malbatan dikarim bi nav bikim. Malek tewrî
selaf...
 
And I can name those families. A family all together...

318
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:37,000
...hatine vê derê, di sala 1850 de, mala Mihiyê Sîlam...
 
...came to this place, in the year 1850, the family of
Mihiyê Sîlam...

319
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:38,000
Mala Eliyê Reşkê.
 
The family of Eliyê Reşkê.

320
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:40,000
Mala Elo Simîn.
 
The family of Elo Simîn.

321
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:42,000
Mala Şêxdada.
 
The family of Şêxdada.

322
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:47,000
Mala Mistiko, li vir em dibêjin mala Hisînê Simo.
 
The family of Mistiko, here we say the family of Hisînê
Simo.

323
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:48,000
Û mala Ebdilfoyê.
 
And the family of Ebdilfoy.

324
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:52,000
Dû re hatine, wek mala Kêmek...
 
Those who came later, like the family of Kêmek...

325
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:55,000
Wek mala Mehmê Reşît û Dadê...
 
Like the family of Mehmê Reşît and Dadê...

326
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:58,000
Wek mala Bêrek.
 
Like the family of Bêrek.

327
00:21:58,000 --> 00:22:08,000
Tê de teqrîben 10 malbat in. Û em gişt xizm û birayên hev
din in û em gişt meyrê hev din in yanî, neha kesê xerîb di
nav me tunene.
 
There are approximately 10 families. And we are all
relatives and brothers, and we are all the people of each
other, meaning, right now there are no strangers among us.

328
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:11,000
Te dît berê, hemî bi eşîrtî dihat naskirin.
 
You see in the past, everything was known by tribes.

329
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:12,000
Erê...
 
Yes...

330
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:22,000
Piştî ew dewlet çêbû... hat gişt li malbatê da naskirin.
Yanî malbat ev navên wan çêbû ne wisa? Berê bi giştî dihat
gotin ji kîjan eşîre... filan eşîra danin.
 
After that state was formed... everything came to be
recognized by family. I mean, they were named as families,
right? In the past, it was generally asked what tribe they
belonged to... they are from such and such tribe.

331
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:27,000
Ê naha gundê we, Gundê Ademo sînorên wî digihêjin kîjan
gundana?
 
And now your village, which villages do the borders of the
Ademo Village reach?

332
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:30,000
Gundê me, li aliyê başûr...
 
Our village, towards the south...

333
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:31,000
Digehê Qerababa.
 
Reaches Qerababa.

334
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:33,000
Û Xirabê Silik.
 
And Xirabê Silik.

335
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:35,000
Û Elbîskê.
 
And Elbîskê.

336
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:37,000
Û 10 kîlometre bi erebeyê em diçin.
 
And we travel 10 kilometers by car.

337
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:39,000
...ji gundê me.
 
...from our village.

338
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:47,000
Li aliyê rojava... Qerabîle, gund bi l'kuhê heye û ew chawa
jî Qerabîle ye.
 
On the west side... Qerabîle, the village is on the mountain
and that plain is also Qerabîle.

339
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:51,000
Tê de zinarek heye, ji wê ra dibêjin Zinarê Sor.
 
Inside it, there is a cliff, they call it the Red Cliff.

340
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:55,000
Û geliyek geliyê Yaşil e. Û du şikeft zêde li vê derê
hene...
 
And a valley, the valley of Yaşil. And there are two main
caves in this place...

341
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:57,000
Şikefta Ebeş...
 
The cave of Ebeş...

342
00:22:57,000 --> 00:22:59,000
Û şikefta Mistiyê Dadê kî.
 
And the cave of Mistiyê Dadê kî.

343
00:22:59,000 --> 00:23:03,000
Û li aliyê bakur, Sê Mala... meydanek heye.
 
And on the north side, Sê Mala... there is a square.

344
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:08,000
Û meydanek mezin heye. Û goristana gundê me jî li aliyê
bakur e.
 
And there is a big square. And the graveyard of our village
is also on the north side.

345
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:14,000
Û li vê derê jî şikeft hene, û sarînc heye û çal hene.
 
And in this place too, there are caves, and there is a
cistern and there are wells.

346
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:19,000
Û li aliyê rojava, sînor e. 3 kîlometro gundê me... sînor...
rojava.
 
And on the west side, is the border. 3 kilometers from our
village... the border... west.

347
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:23,000
Ew deşt deşta gundê me ye. Dîsa şikeft hene...
 
That plain is the plain of our village. Again, there are
caves...

348
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:26,000
Û ziyaretek jî heye, ji wê re dibêjin Yaxmûr Dede.
 
And there is also a shrine, they call it Yaxmûr Dede.

349
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:39,000
Ev gava baran nebarîse... em di berê serê salê da çêdikin,
em deran qurbaniyê xwe dibin wê derê, wek kevir dikin wê
zêde...
 
When the rain doesn't fall... in the past, at the start of
the year, we would take our sacrifices there, as stones we
would make them more...

350
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:40,000
Ew li kîjan derê ye dikeve?
 
Where is that located?

351
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:46,000
Ev li ser sînor e, li aliyê rojava navê gundekî... navê gund
jî Yaxmûr Dede ye.
 
This is on the border, on the west side, the name of a
village... the name of the village is also Yaxmûr Dede.

352
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:48,000
Sê kîlometre gundê me ji wê dûr e.
 
Our village is three kilometers away from it.

353
00:23:48,000 --> 00:23:51,000
Ê naha, berê di gundê we de rîspiyên we kê bûn?
 
And now, in the past, who were the elders in your village?

354
00:23:51,000 --> 00:23:57,000
Te dît her gundekî da, odeyek mêvanan hebû, yan rîspiyên vî
gundî hebûn.
 
You see, in every village, there used to be a guest room, or
there were elders of the village.

355
00:23:57,000 --> 00:24:02,000
Ew çareseriyek di gundê we hebûna çareserkirin dikirin, naha
wek wan nîne jixwe... Niha jî komîn ava bûn e.
 
If there was a solution to be made in your village, they
would solve it, now it is not like them of course... Now
communes have been established.

356
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:03,000
Erê...
 
Yes...

357
00:24:03,000 --> 00:24:05,000
Ê di wê demê de berê kê bû, rîspiyên we kê bûn?
 
And in that time before, who was it, who were your elders?

358
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:08,000
Berê, Simalî Elî hebû.
 
Before, there was Simalî Elî.

359
00:24:08,000 --> 00:24:12,000
Simalî Eliyê Reşk e... Mistiko hebû...
 
Simalî Eliyê Reşk e... there was Mistiko...

360
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:14,000
Hase hebû, bapîrê me bû.
 
There was Hase, he was our grandfather.

361
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:16,000
Bakirê Şêxda hebû.
 
There was Bakirê Şêxda.

362
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:21,000
Zemanek... vana, odiya Simalî Elî hebû.
 
For a time... these, Simalî Elî's guest room existed.

363
00:24:21,000 --> 00:24:26,000
Gava mişkîleyek hebûna, gava îdek bihatana, her kesî
sêniyek... şîvê xwe dikişandin...
 
When there was a problem, when a holiday would come,
everyone would pull their plate... their dinner...

364
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:33,000
Wan sibehiyên îdê xwe dikirin, da'wî dikişandin. Eger
mişkîleyek hebûya, gava teqîqek bi wê re hal dikirin.
 
They would do this on holiday mornings, drawing invitations.
If there was a problem, immediately they would solve it with
that.

365
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:38,000
Neha jî, komîn heye, û komîn wa we wacibê wî însanî radibe.
 
Now too, there is the commune, and the commune fulfills the
duty of that person.

366
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:40,000
Mala we ava bibe... Xwedê kêmasiya we nede.
 
May your house be built... May God not give you
shortcomings.

367
00:24:40,000 --> 00:25:00,000
Seheta we jî xweş. Silav û selam li Gundê Ademo bi qanatiya
Ronahî. Û baxwa we re te...
 
Good health to you too. Greetings and salutations to the
Village of Ademo with the Ronahî channel. And your garden...

368
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:19,000
Li rojhilatê gund, Çiyayê Qerabêlê, Binê Sor... Geliyê
Yaşilê dikevin.
 
To the east of the village, lie the Qerabêlê Mountain, Binê
Sor... and the Yaşil Valley.

369
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:24,000
Li vir du şikeft hene, bi navê Mistî Dede têne naskirin.
 
Here there are two caves, known by the name of Mistî Dede.

370
00:25:24,000 --> 00:25:30,000
Li başûrê gund Xirabê Solik, gundê Qerababa, Elbîskê û Pira
Hesarê dikevin.
 
To the south of the village lie Xirabê Solik, the village of
Qerababa, Elbîskê, and the Hesar Bridge.

371
00:25:30,000 --> 00:25:33,000
Herweha li vir ziyareteyek bi navê Selo heye.
 
Also, there is a shrine here named Selo.

372
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:37,000
Berî gundek hebûye. Bi navê Selo dihat naskirin.
 
Before, there was a village. It was known by the name Selo.

373
00:25:37,000 --> 00:25:46,000
Ev gund neha xirab bûye û ji ber ku şerek navbera qewmê Kurd
de çêbûye ew qewm cihê xwe berdaye. Niha tenê goristanek û
sarîncek li şûna vî gundî mane.
 
This village has now been ruined, and because a war occurred
among the Kurdish people, those people abandoned their
place. Now, only a graveyard and a cistern remain in the
place of this village.

374
00:25:46,000 --> 00:25:52,000
Li rojavayê gund sînorê Bakurê Kurdistanê ye, ku tenê 3
Kîlometreyan ji gund dûr e.
 
To the west of the village is the border of Northern
Kurdistan, which is only 3 kilometers away from the village.

375
00:25:52,000 --> 00:25:57,000
Herweha rêza vê derê deşt e herweha û dirêjiya wê dighêje
Efrînê.
 
Also, the row of this area is a plain and its length reaches
Afrin.

376
00:25:57,000 --> 00:26:01,000
Herweha ziyaretek bi navê Yaxmûr Dede, ku li ser sînorê ne,
dikevin.
 
Also, a shrine named Yaxmûr Dede, which is on the border, is
situated here.

377
00:26:01,000 --> 00:26:21,000
Piraniya sirninc li derdora vê ziyareta ava dikirin e û
baxçeyên sepze û fêkî yan.
 
Most of the cisterns were built around this shrine, along
with gardens of vegetables and fruits.

378
00:26:43,000 --> 00:26:44,000
Merheba dayê...
 
Hello mother...

379
00:26:44,000 --> 00:26:46,000
Ehlan we sehlan hûn b'xêr hatin.
 
Welcome, you are welcome.

380
00:26:46,000 --> 00:26:49,000
Hûn bi ser sera me hatin... hûn bi ser çava me hatin... hûn
bi xêr û xweşî bin.
 
You came upon our heads... you came upon our eyes... may you
be well and happy.

381
00:26:49,000 --> 00:26:56,000
Spas dayê te em bi xêr û xweşî bin. Dema em derbasî gundan
dibin, em jî bi rastî kêfxweş dibin. Dema em dayikan di
gundan de dibînin.
 
Thank you mother, may we be well and happy. When we visit
villages, we genuinely become happy. When we see mothers in
the villages.

382
00:26:56,000 --> 00:27:05,000
Dayê ka em qala Gundê Ademo bikin. Berê çi diqewimiya? Demên
bihûrî de... em bi kurtasî de em behsa lîstika bikin.
 
Mother, let's talk about the Village of Ademo. What used to
happen in the past? In the times passed... let's talk
briefly about the games.

383
00:27:05,000 --> 00:27:07,000
Û te behsa lîstikek kir.
 
And you mentioned a game.

384
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:11,000
Me berê behsa gelek lîstoka kir. Lîstika me hebû, b'lî
l'ayê.
 
We talked about many games before. We had a game, 'bilî
layê'.

385
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:14,000
Em du... gundî kom dibîn, qîz, şeş-heft yan pazdeh-bîstik em
kom dibîn.
 
We two... villagers would gather, girls, six-seven or
fifteen-twenty of us would gather.

386
00:27:14,000 --> 00:27:17,000
Em didan di we da dilîstin bi sê-çar ro.
 
We would give and play in that for three-four days.

387
00:27:17,000 --> 00:27:22,000
Di cejna da... erê di cejna de qirnî tiştî dikir.. am ew
dilîstin, qerç dikişandin û me dilîstin.
 
During the holidays... yes, during the holidays we would
make things... we played that, we'd draw lines and play.

388
00:27:22,000 --> 00:27:24,000
Ordek qamçî sipî dikir û dilîstin.
 
A duck, we would make a whip white and play.

389
00:27:24,000 --> 00:27:28,000
Em dîtir me dikir diçîn... ji vir diçûn nîşe.. deqaşandin.
 
The rest of us would go... from here we went and aimed..
pulled it.

390
00:27:28,000 --> 00:27:36,000
Em de kinc me bervê didan di nav we da.. hûr dikirin e zar
zaro.. bi vi xalî dilîstn e vî ro.
 
We'd push clothes towards it inside that... chop it finely
for the kids... with this carpet they played on this day.

391
00:27:36,000 --> 00:27:38,000
Yanî jiyana berê... jiyana berê pir xweş bû yan...
 
So the life in the past... the old life was very good or...

392
00:27:38,000 --> 00:27:40,000
Jiyana berê ji ya niha xweştir bû!
 
The old life was better than now!

393
00:27:40,000 --> 00:27:42,000
O berê... hin qas cefa de hebu na...
 
And before... there was some hardship, no...

394
00:27:42,000 --> 00:27:47,000
Tu zanî em bê çek derdîn, bi hef r'o... diçîn çolê dî da
bçîn. Belkî bîst jinik wek em dîçîn bi havre...
 
You know we went out without weapons, in seven days... went
to the wild, we went. Maybe twenty women like us went
together...

395
00:27:47,000 --> 00:27:54,000
Em bi havre rê, şelekî xwe me dikişandin... qîz em ê bihavre
diçîn zeva ca, am we derê ro kar dikir, û weha şelekê me
l'da dî hilda, dayika me bûn, yê em em am diçîn e wera l'vir
de.
 
Together on the road, we pulled our bundles... as girls we
went to the field together, we worked there during the day,
and like that she lifted our bundle, they were our mothers,
those of us who went there from here.

396
00:27:54,000 --> 00:27:58,000
Çi dayika me bû, Çi xaltîka me, yan emca me bûn, wek em
dîçûn ro ro kîha...
 
Whether it was our mother, or our aunt, or our uncle, as we
went day by day there...

397
00:27:58,000 --> 00:28:00,000
Belkî bîst mêr em deçîn bi hevdî derê dikişandin e...
 
Maybe twenty men of us went together to pull it...

398
00:28:00,000 --> 00:28:04,000
Rîya me bi de avê re, em dçûn e wê derê me ciyê xwe di got
Kevirê Vahasê. Em di çî dî av dorê vî hesê.
 
Our path was by the water, we went. There we called our
place Vahase's Stone. We went around this stone.

399
00:28:04,000 --> 00:28:05,000
Kevirek lî wir hey e...
 
Is there a stone there...

400
00:28:05,000 --> 00:28:08,000
Kevir we lî der bû, noka wî gî xalî kir. Ew bo lî vî de
hîlkira...
 
A stone was there, now it's completely empty. They lifted it
for this...

401
00:28:08,000 --> 00:28:15,000
Em dîçe we de dorî Kevirê Vahasê. Ew de teqîzan vî de wî
de... ew me ke dori we de. ew bi gî şelak ew girtin ew
hildan
 
We went around Vahase's Stone. They'd put pieces here and
there... we would circle it. They completely grabbed the
bundle and lifted it.

402
00:28:15,000 --> 00:28:18,000
Te behsa şalek qir... giram bû çewa te de dikin şelek?
 
You mentioned the bundle... it was heavy, how did you make
the bundle?

403
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:21,000
Na her kes gora xwe de kêşandin.
 
No, everyone pulled according to their ability.

404
00:28:21,000 --> 00:28:24,000
Bes a wî qas bû y bi hevdî himbêz dikir, jinik jê ji dî
hemêz de di kir.
 
But there was so much that they embraced it together, a
woman from it also embraced it.

405
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:29,000
Jin i d t pş te k, yik a n p ser di da k i b r n .
 
A woman put it on her back, another put it on her head to
carry it.

406
00:28:29,000 --> 00:28:33,000
Yani go am b ro c am t di l e am b he i r d te am am ro d o
ko ...
 
Meaning, as we spent the day, we went and with each other,
we went through the day like that...

407
00:28:33,000 --> 00:28:38,000
Nêha ko , me ni şeleko ti tîştek em t ro i i bi he ro ba m
am k ti t e te ...
 
But now, we don't bring the bundle or anything, we just stay
with each other during the day...

408
00:28:38,000 --> 00:28:44,000
Wekî ko em ro l k in em bo in t ko i a da p ro bi na r p a k
do mi ro am te x p in em ta b bi ne x b ti a de ...
 
Like when we go out, we see things in the day, we go around
and up until today we still do things together...

409
00:28:44,000 --> 00:28:49,000
Bes cilê nêha t i ba do w ro g me em ro ro ... do x e g m wa
ma bi em n
 
But the clothes now, we don't do it the same way every
day... we just stay as we are.

410
00:28:49,000 --> 00:28:52,000
Û qîz nêha xwe ji we hîn me d em t ?
 
And do the girls now learn from you?

411
00:28:52,000 --> 00:28:54,000
Da e ki me ew bo ko m w we ko na em tu k em r w ba w tu e tu
 
Our mothers used to be like that, but we didn't learn
anything from them.

412
00:28:54,000 --> 00:29:00,000
We ki l va in r de me l em t p a di i p i t bi ba wa l m a p
am q do ta x in te ...
 
Like those now who work and read, we didn't do things like
that, we just stayed at home...

413
00:29:00,000 --> 00:29:02,000
W n x ko di l ba r am b el di ro a em a n l
 
You didn't learn those things back then.

414
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:08,000
Xw o x d me da w do ew me m b t ro w f em bo tişt ba q e a l
na m am
 
We just lived our days and didn't learn those things.

415
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:14,000
Da ye, tîşek ez te pirs kim... av ji kîjan derê dianî?
Kaniyê te derî av wa bo i am
 
Mother, let me ask you something... where did you bring
water from? Was there a spring to bring water?

416
00:29:14,000 --> 00:29:16,000
M af l qa n i k k re de we e dî
 
We had a spring, we brought water from there.

417
00:29:16,000 --> 00:29:18,000
Av me de da o wa ra t me a af b am dî dî af we p d ma de me
q n bi d p o d m q u p g n y b g n
 
We gave water and brought water from it, we saw the water,
we brought our pots and filled them...

418
00:29:18,000 --> 00:29:24,000
G li ro me di bi in a q we g m bo ko am o b ba y am ko m te
e ko ro am in d de ...
 
We took them during the day and kept them for when we
gathered, so we had water when we stayed...

419
00:29:24,000 --> 00:29:31,000
M g t ko we we r go we em am n c l a m y m q r l te de go di
p s b ko u f w y ma m ...
 
We took them like that, we brought the clothes and washed
them there, we did our things...

420
00:29:31,000 --> 00:29:34,000
M a o w d em a p ro g k t em em ba g b ma d o ...
 
You played a lot in those times...

421
00:29:34,000 --> 00:29:39,000
A r a b u di bo u l ti ke sa k em l da o de x e m ...
 
Give me the name of one game so we can mention it.

422
00:29:39,000 --> 00:29:50,000
La d p d wa d me m a f m di o di ra na f i q b ti wa w k m q
b t w b e di l ls p e bi ma a a m bo o
 
We played games with water, and other things we found
around, we made up games to play.

423
00:29:50,000 --> 00:30:00,000
Gelek lîstik hene lî vî gund i da.
 
There are many games in this village.

424
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:06,000
dileyîzin, kobaka dileyîzin, êşta xisar û çêdikin dileyîzin,
dîsan wekî yên zorikan dileyîzin.
 
we play, we play kobaka, well we make a line and play, again
we play like the young ones.

425
00:30:06,000 --> 00:30:14,000
Ê am ji êşta adetê meye berê, êşta em sê-çor mesela keçik
bav diketin.
 
Well, this is our custom from the past, well we, three or
four girls for example would get together.

426
00:30:14,000 --> 00:30:20,000
Em yekî va dinê li wî darê, am destê xwe jî da wî, û yek jî
em herin wanê êşta yekî dever keve.
 
We place one against that tree, we also put our hands on it,
and one also we go like that, well one gets in front.

427
00:30:20,000 --> 00:30:24,000
Haw kî di ro rabibe. Êşta me jî va ro kîv dikir.
 
So that the other one gets up. Well, we also used to aim at
this one.

428
00:30:24,000 --> 00:30:28,000
Me dikana. Me lê dixist. Ev jî bas di nav xulê dibî.
 
We were able to. We would hit her. She would just end up in
the dust.

429
00:30:28,000 --> 00:30:33,000
Êşta nika jî am me qaçikê hazir kirîye, cuwê me jî anîye em
konin bileyîzin.
 
Well, now too we have prepared the clothes, we brought our
sticks, we want to play.

430
00:30:33,000 --> 00:30:35,000
Nika gellek... hûn çend kes bileyîzin?
 
Now many... how many of you play?

431
00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:39,000
Gerek qalçîyande yek, çor bin pênc bin.
 
It needs at least one, four or five.

432
00:30:39,000 --> 00:30:41,000
Çor-pênc kes bileyîzin.
 
Four or five people play.

433
00:30:41,000 --> 00:30:42,000
Yanî didu bi didu dileyîzin?
 
Meaning two by two play?

434
00:30:42,000 --> 00:30:48,000
Na. Yek wê wextî qulibî du xira dikê, va dinê.
 
No. One, when she rolls it, two ruin it, they place it.

435
00:30:48,000 --> 00:30:54,000
Em êşta çor ji mesela evê cuwê xwe da vî diqulibînin, êşta
am wa dileyîzin.
 
And we, well four of us for example, roll our sticks into
this one, well this is how we play.

436
00:30:54,000 --> 00:31:14,000
Ê nika emê bibînin. Belê temaşevanên hêja, de ka emê hev re
lîstikê dayîkan jî temaşe kin.
 
Well now we will see. Yes, dear viewers, come let's also
watch the mothers' game together.

437
00:33:18,000 --> 00:33:22,000
Li bakurê gund, bajarokê Meydan Ekbez, gundê Meydana dikeve.
 
To the north of the village, lies the town of Meydan Ekbez,
the village of Meydana.

438
00:33:22,000 --> 00:33:29,000
Goristana gund li bakurê gund e. Û deştekê freh bi navê
Deşta Wêranşarê jî heye.
 
The village cemetery is in the north of the village. And
there is also a wide plain called the Plain of Weranshar.

439
00:33:29,000 --> 00:33:32,000
Her weha çar pakrewan ji gundê Adema hene.
 
Also, there are four martyrs from the village of Adema.

440
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:37,000
Ku di demên curebicure de, di şerê rizgariya neteweyî de
şehîd bûne.
 
Who were martyred at various times, in the war of national
liberation.

441
00:33:37,000 --> 00:33:42,000
Şehîd Ferîd, Merwan, Berxwedan Efrîn û Şehîd Kurd Efrîn.
 
Martyr Ferid, Merwan, Berxwedan Efrin and Martyr Kurd Efrin.

442
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:47,000
Her weha komîna gund bi navê Şehîd Merwan hatiye binavkirin.
 
Also, the village commune has been named after Martyr
Merwan.

443
00:33:47,000 --> 00:34:02,000
Dibistana seretayî ya gund jî bi navê Şehîd Ferîd hatiye
binavkirin.
 
The primary school of the village has also been named after
Martyr Ferid.

444
00:34:02,000 --> 00:34:05,000
Pazdeh bîrên avê di gund de hene.
 
There are fifteen water wells in the village.

445
00:34:05,000 --> 00:34:08,000
Gundî ava vexwarinê jê peyda dikin.
 
The villagers obtain drinking water from them.

446
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:14,000
Digel avdana baxçe û darên xwe, her weha pezên xwe û sewalên
xwe jî pê av didin.
 
Along with watering their gardens and trees, they also give
water to their sheep and livestock with them.

447
00:34:14,000 --> 00:34:17,000
Xirabek bi navê Xirabê Ebdû heye.
 
There is a ruin named the Ruin of Ebdû.

448
00:34:17,000 --> 00:34:20,000
Çar şikeft tê de hene.
 
There are four caves in it.

449
00:34:20,000 --> 00:34:23,000
Û kaniyek a avê jî bi navê Kaniya Korikê heye.
 
And there is a water spring named the Spring of Korik.

450
00:34:23,000 --> 00:34:43,000
Berê gundiyan serdana wê dikirin, cil û bergên xwe li ber
kaniyê dişûştin.
 
In the past, the villagers used to visit it, washing their
clothes by the spring.

451
00:34:55,000 --> 00:34:59,000
Belê temaşevanên hêja. Li vir jî em gihiştin dawiya
bernameya xwe.
 
Yes, dear viewers. Here we have also reached the end of our
program.

452
00:34:59,000 --> 00:35:04,000
Îro jî em li gundê Adema bûn. Lê di dawiya dawî apo Xelîl
xwest stranekê ji me re bêje.
 
Today we were also in the village of Adema. But at the very
end, uncle Xelîl wanted to sing a song for us.

453
00:35:04,000 --> 00:35:08,000
Em spasiya wî dikin. Û em spasiya millet dikin, hemî yên li
derdora me.
 
We thank him. And we thank the people, everyone around us.

454
00:35:08,000 --> 00:35:13,000
Berê çawa şahî li gund dibûn, berê stran çawa dihatin gotin,
niha jî apo Xelîl ê ji me re behs bike.
 
How celebrations were in the village in the past, how songs
used to be sung, now uncle Xelîl will tell us about it.

455
00:35:13,000 --> 00:35:16,000
Û wê stranekê ji me re bêje.
 
And he will sing a song for us.

456
00:35:16,000 --> 00:35:17,000
Merheba apê Xelîl.
 
Hello uncle Xelîl.

457
00:35:17,000 --> 00:35:18,000
Ehlawesahlan, merheba.
 
Welcome, hello.

458
00:35:18,000 --> 00:35:22,000
Em dixwazin tu hinekî behsa şahiyê berê bikî. Berê çawa şahî
dihatin kirin?
 
We want you to talk a little about the celebrations of the
past. How were celebrations done in the past?

459
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:26,000
Ehlewesahlan, ser serê min û ser çavên min. Xwastkê te, berê
şahî...
 
Welcome, upon my head and upon my eyes. As you asked, in the
past celebrations...

460
00:35:26,000 --> 00:35:30,000
xelat dikirin, xwendî dihatin, def di lê dixistin.
 
they gave gifts, educated people came, they played the drum.

461
00:35:30,000 --> 00:35:33,000
Def, zirne, êşta kilam digotin.
 
Drum, zurna, well they sang songs.

462
00:35:33,000 --> 00:35:39,000
Dîlan digerandin. Ev tiştina hebûn.
 
They danced. These things existed.

463
00:35:39,000 --> 00:35:40,000
Te kîve kilam digotin di gundan da?
 
Where did you sing songs in the villages?

464
00:35:40,000 --> 00:35:44,000
Di gundan de, ez hebûm, Hisûyê Bilê hebû,
 
In the villages, there was me, there was Hisûyê Bilê,

465
00:35:44,000 --> 00:35:48,000
yekî bi navê Hisên hebû, Hisênê Bekirê Şêx didan.
 
there was someone named Hisên, they called him Hisênê Bekirê
Şêx.

466
00:35:48,000 --> 00:35:50,000
Êşta vana kilam digotin. Bûk derdixistin.
 
Well, these ones sang songs. They brought out the bride.

467
00:35:50,000 --> 00:35:54,000
Me diçû dighêştin mal. Xwedê yanî xêr lê bike û êşta,
 
We would go and reach the house. May God bring goodness and
well,

468
00:35:54,000 --> 00:35:57,000
me waha gotinek dikir. Me wa govend dikirin.
 
we would sing like that. We danced like that.

469
00:35:57,000 --> 00:35:59,000
Ê we stranên we çi bûn di dema dawetan? We çi kilam digotin?
 
Well, what were your songs during weddings? What songs did
you sing?

470
00:35:59,000 --> 00:36:02,000
Stranên me kilamên de kêm bûn. Gulê zer bûn,
 
Our songs, songs were few. It was Gulê zer,

471
00:36:02,000 --> 00:36:04,000
êşta Fêrûz bûn. Hema kilamên wilo bûn.
 
well it was Fêrûz. Just songs like that.

472
00:36:04,000 --> 00:36:05,000
Kilamên govendê?
 
Dance songs?

473
00:36:05,000 --> 00:36:08,000
Ê nûv bû, leyl bû. Êşta evna bûn. Yanî.
 
Well, it was slow, it was night. Well, it was these.
Meaning.

474
00:36:08,000 --> 00:36:13,000
Kîlam hebin hene, yek jî dîn hene. We ra ez dixwazim
hilbijêrim bistirim.
 
There are songs, there are also others. Come, I want to
choose and sing.

475
00:36:13,000 --> 00:36:14,000
Kîjanê ji me re bêjî?
 
Which one will you sing for us?

476
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:16,000
Ê wê Gulê zer dibêjim.
 
Well, I will sing that Gulê zer.

477
00:36:16,000 --> 00:36:19,000
Û millet ê jî li te vegere ne wilo? Te çi got ew jî ê li te
vegerînin.
 
And the people will repeat after you, right? Whatever you
said, they will also repeat after you.

478
00:36:19,000 --> 00:36:21,000
Wek berê. Çawa am ji wan...
 
Like in the past. How we from them...

479
00:36:21,000 --> 00:36:24,000
Wek berê. Me çû dawîyê, gundî jî li pey me bi bûn.
 
Like in the past. We went to weddings, the villagers were
also behind us.

480
00:36:24,000 --> 00:36:27,000
Kelîme bi kelîme yanî şor bi şor.
 
Word by word, meaning sentence by sentence.

481
00:36:27,000 --> 00:36:28,000
Temam. Kerem ke.
 
Alright. Go ahead.

482
00:36:28,000 --> 00:36:30,000
Bêrin.
 
Let's go.

483
00:36:30,000 --> 00:36:31,000
Saeta we xweş.
 
Have a good time.

484
